<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-15T00:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-15T00:29:00-05:00" n="506" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1226</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-15T00:00:00-05:29">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1917,
                                midnight</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>President Menocal received from two representatives of Government in
                            Santiago following cablegram tonight: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Interpreting your wishes and policy we today visited Mayor
                                    Comacho, liberal, who had taken refuge in Italian Consulate,
                                    assured him in your name he will be absolutely unmolested and
                                    respected in position as mayor. We asked him make our attitude
                                    plain to all liberals here, stating your Government opposed to
                                    all reprisals, and only desire prompt complete restoration
                                    public peace and tranquillity.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>The President cabled reply as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>I applaud your conduct with respect to Mayor Comacho. Continue to
                                    employ these methods.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>